axis: stack-safety-deep-effect-recursion
status: pending-runtime
needs: stack-safe (heap-allocated) effect continuation on the portable VM
measured: effect-performing recursion is stack-safe at depth 500 but overflows
  between 500 and 2000 (`java.lang.StackOverflowError` at 2000/8000/50000) on BOTH
  portable-VM tiers — `ssc run` (interp) and `ssc run --bytecode` (2026-07-14). Pure
  tail recursion is unaffected (axis-03 ✓ at 2,000,000); only recursion that PERFORMS
  an effect per frame grows the native stack. Corroborates codex-interop's audit
  ("legacy deep-handler/return paths recursively stack-unsafe").
  Tracked: BUGS.md `control-interop-effect-recursion-stack-unsafe`.
expected: no unbounded managed/native stack growth for deep effect-performing
  computations (§14.1 "stack safety"). Cross-language mixed TCO (§14.2, depth
  ≥1,000,000) additionally requires the host value/call bridge.
